post_cb({"8804643": {"CommentCount": "9", "ViewCount": "942", "CreationDate": "2012-01-10T14:13:52.510", "LastActivityDate": "2012-01-10T14:29:35.637", "Title": "how to abort a c++ program and exit with status 0?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "8804676", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "8804643", "Score": "2", "Body": "<p>I want to kill my c++ program and terminate immediately without activating destructors of any kind,  especially static and global variables, but I want to exit with status 0 - <code>abort()</code> will not work for me.</p>\n<p>Does anyone have a solution?\nThanks</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><abort>", "OwnerUserId": "963564", "AnswerCount": "3"}, "8804676": {"ParentId": "8804643", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "4", "Body": "<p>Maybe <code>_exit(0);</code> is what you're looking for?</p>\n<p>Here is the <a href=\"http://www.kernel.org/doc/man-pages/online/pages/man2/exit.2.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">man page</a> to read up about it.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "410824", "LastEditorUserId": "410824", "LastEditDate": "2012-01-10T14:27:01.273", "Id": "8804676", "Score": "8", "CreationDate": "2012-01-10T14:16:45.853", "LastActivityDate": "2012-01-10T14:27:01.273"}, "8804672": {"ParentId": "8804643", "CommentCount": "4", "Body": "<p>How about <a href=\"http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/_exit.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>_Exit(0)</code></a> from <code>stdlib.h</code>. (Demo: <a href=\"http://ideone.com/ecCgC\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://ideone.com/ecCgC</a>)</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "224671", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "8804672", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2012-01-10T14:16:18.477", "LastActivityDate": "2012-01-10T14:16:18.477"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_8804643_8804701_0": {"section_id": 6800, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}, "n3337": {"so_8804643_8804701_0": {"section_id": 6555, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}, "n4659": {"so_8804643_8804701_0": {"section_id": 8290, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "length": 13}}}, "8804701": {"ParentId": "8804643", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>From C++11 n3290 - \u00a7 18.5:</p>\n<pre><code>[[noreturn]] void _Exit(int status) noexcept;\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_8804643_8804701_0\">The program is terminated without executing destructors for objects of automatic, thread, or\n  static storage duration and without calling functions passed to atexit()</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is actually defined in C99 though so in practice works on a large number of pre-C++11 implementations.</p>\n<p>Use:</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;cstdlib&gt;\n#include &lt;iostream&gt;\n\nstruct test {\n  ~test() {\n    std::cout &lt;&lt; \"Goodbye world\" &lt;&lt; std::endl;\n  }\n};\n\nint main() {\n  test t;\n  _Exit(0);\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "168175", "LastEditorUserId": "168175", "LastEditDate": "2012-01-10T14:29:35.637", "Id": "8804701", "Score": "6", "CreationDate": "2012-01-10T14:18:22.853", "LastActivityDate": "2012-01-10T14:29:35.637"}});